[Mr. Cathcart says]136 [he has had "a lot of fun" at Kidder,]137
[adding]138 [the crack]139 [about his being a "tool-and-die man"]140
[never bothered him.]141 ["It was an absolutely marvelous line and
one]142 [I used many times,"]143 [he says.]144

[Smiling broadly]145 [when he talks about Mr. Carpenter,]146
[Mr. Cathcart says]147 [the new Kidder chief is "going to be
recognized shortly as one of the real leaders in the
